# Starting the server

When the user asks to "start the server", "restart the server", or "run the server",
**default to running the Vite dev server**:

```bash
npm run dev
```

- Run it from the `app/` directory (that's where the `dev` script lives).
- Prefer this over `npm start` / `node server/main.js`, which only serves the
  pre-built `app/dist` bundle and will NOT reflect frontend source changes.
- Start it in the background (long-running process); don't block on it.
